<div class="post-message " data-role="message" dir="auto">

<p>Thanks for the stupid "straw man" attack.</p><p>Nobody here suggested that China is a democracy. What I and others have been saying is, American nationalists and jingoists are whining about China engaging in a very mild version of the gunboat diplomacy that has been engaged in by the United States, for over a century now. It was just fine and dandy when it was done by English-speaking white people, but oh, my goodness! We can't let those yellow Chinese play "our" little imperialist game.</p><p>Well, sorry, squire... nonsense propaganda of this type may play very well in Topeka, but it doesn't play very well at all in, say, Shanghai... not to mention Jakarta.</p>

</div>

