<div class="post-body-inner">

<div class="post-message-container" data-role="message-container">

<div class="publisher-anchor-color" data-role="message-content">
<div class="post-message " data-role="message" dir="auto">

<p>International norms have changed since the 19th century.  The 19th and 20th Century imperial powers (which included an enthusiastic Japan) caused such chaos and suffering that they themselves created a newer, better order.  China doesn't need to prove, again, that aggressive colony building and military adventurism are destructive.  We have enough of a reminder of that from the US as it is (but the US doesn't attempt territorial expansion, for whatever that's worth).</p>

</div>

