<p>In those ' violations of Mexican sovereignty ' how many Mexican Soldiers were killed?</p><p>Mexico had a tradition of border violations, see the Dawson Massacre, since they never recognized Texas independence or them joining the USA.</p><p>They didn't follow the Treaties of Velasco, dispite Santa Anna signing them.</p>

