<a href="http://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2014/11/chinas-dangerous-game/380789/#comment-1633728364" data-role="relative-time" class="time-ago" title="Monday, October 13, 2014 8:43 PM">4 days ago</a>

</span>


</header>


<div class="post-body-inner">

<div class="post-message-container" data-role="message-container">

<div class="publisher-anchor-color" data-role="message-content">
<div class="post-message " data-role="message" dir="auto">

<p>Well, it has forced China to become more Western. They have more English speakers than ever before. They consume Western goods and media en-masse. They've absorbed and learned a great deal from us.</p><p>Oh, you meant become "more democratic"! Ha. Well, sorry, no. It doesn't work that way.</p>

</div>

