<div class="post-body-inner">

<div class="post-message-container" data-role="message-container">

<div class="publisher-anchor-color" data-role="message-content">
<div class="post-message " data-role="message" dir="auto">

<p>"He said it would force China to become more western. Instead, it has created a country with a much better military and a dangerous desire to bully its neighbors."</p><p>1) Clinton was wrong because no country can force another to become more "anything".</p><p>2) Admitting the PRC into the World Trade Organization did not create a country with a much better military and a dangerous desire to bully its neighbors. If that was the PRC's long term goal, they would have done it anyway.</p><p>The USA (my country) is not responsible for every bad thing or good thing that happens in the world. The rest of the world has its own agenda.</p>

</div>

