<div class="post-body-inner">

<div class="post-message-container" data-role="message-container">

<div class="publisher-anchor-color" data-role="message-content">
<div class="post-message " data-role="message" dir="auto">

<p>Yes, your argument is in fact a red herring.  And a fat juicy one at that.  Even the southern states opted to fully rejoin the union (although I will concede it was a little like the situation in Tibet) after the civil war.  What you are implying is that what, every generation should have a vote on what country they want to be part of?  If that were to take place, the US would still very likely have 50 states.  China would be TIbetless.</p>

</div>

