<div class="post-body-inner">

<div class="post-message-container" data-role="message-container">

<div class="publisher-anchor-color" data-role="message-content">
<div class="post-message " data-role="message" dir="auto">

<p>I think that if every generation had a vote on what country they'd be part of, Hong Kong might leave China but I believe that in Tibet, it will be either a very close match or they will not leave.</p><p>Of course I could be wrong. Remember that migrants are not representative of whole populations. There are some Mandarin speaking Tibetans that I've met who are not pro independence. But from what I remember I think the Dalai Lama doesn't support complete independence either. </p>

</div>

