<div class="post-message " data-role="message" dir="auto">

<p>There isn't a dispute, because there's no such thing as Tibet, at least as far as the nation-state system is concerned. It would be like saying "the dispute between the US and the Lakota Nation"; the Lakota may argue that they're a conquered people whose land was taken from them, but there was never a Lakota nation-state as such that was recognized by the world. Tibet? Same.</p>

</div>

