<div class="post-body-inner">

<div class="post-message-container" data-role="message-container">

<div class="publisher-anchor-color" data-role="message-content">
<div class="post-message " data-role="message" dir="auto">

<p>Honestly according to the Westphalian nation-state concept, many non-Western societies were not 'states' until quite recently. But they were countries, with governments, and with an idea of being a country.</p><p>Now I'm not pro-free Tibet. but Tibet definitely had its own form of governance and was a diverse place historically.</p>

</div>

