<div class="post-message " data-role="message" dir="auto">

<p>don't know why Indonesia is not discussed more in these conversations about east Asian geopolitics.  they have a huge population, a large land mass, and they control a lot of the navigable waterways from the Indian Ocean into these disputed areas.  also happens to be a Muslim country.</p><p>China has a lot to deal with.  the environment could collapse before any of this territorial stuff matters.</p>

</div>

