<p>If the US do not beef up their West Pacific presence, it will be like Eastern Europe in 1939. Someone will come and grab it. Nature abhors vacuum and aggressive dictatorial regimes abhor weak neighbors not taken over yet. <br>It was all explained by Winston Churchill about 80 years ago so it is a choice of either read or replay.</p>

