</a>
</div>


<div class="post-body">
<header>
<span class="post-byline">

<span class="author publisher-anchor-color"><a href="#" data-action="profile" data-user="44187675" data-username="Testerty" data-role="username">Testerty</a></span>






</span>

<span class="post-meta">
<span class="bullet time-ago-bullet" aria-hidden="true">•</span>


<a href="http://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2014/11/chinas-dangerous-game/380789/#comment-1635343228" data-role="relative-time" class="time-ago" title="Tuesday, October 14, 2014 6:54 PM">3 days ago</a>

</span>


</header>


<div class="post-body-inner">

<div class="post-message-container" data-role="message-container">

<div class="publisher-anchor-color" data-role="message-content">
<div class="post-message " data-role="message" dir="auto">

<p>The Nine-Dash Line was established by the current Taiwanese government in 1934. At that time, nobody contest the claim. In fact, its ally USA even endorsed it. The 2 China are in tune on the Nine-Dash Line i.e. South China Sea belongs to China. Only one China has the capability to enforce this claim.</p>

</div>

