<header class="discovery-post-header">
<h3 title="When a Baby Born in Australia Isn't Australian">
<span data-role="discovery-thread-title" class="title line-truncate" data-line-truncate="2">
When a Baby Born in Australia Isn't Australian
</span>



</h3>


<ul class="meta">

<li class="comments">


50 comments


</li>


<li class="time">14 hours ago</li>

</ul>

</header>



</a><a href="http://redirect.disqus.com/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Finternational%2Farchive%2F2014%2F10%2Fwhen-a-baby-born-in-australia-isnt-australian%2F381549%2F%3A2Ay_SyFeubNk8Bhl2oBQg2Q5Pgk&amp;imp=3918o8b34llpir&amp;prev_imp=3907q8e3mg4taq&amp;forum_id=292591&amp;forum=theatlantic&amp;thread_id=3112115300&amp;major_version=metadata&amp;user_id=106760165&amp;thread=3124699552&amp;zone=internal_discovery" class="top-comment" data-role="discovery-top-comment">
<img alt="Avatar" data-role="discovery-avatar" src="//a.disquscdn.com/uploads/users/5629/7822/avatar92.jpg?1384482430">
<p><span class="user" data-role="discovery-top-comment-author">Cincinnatus</span> — <span data-role="discovery-top-comment-snippet" class="line-truncate" data-line-truncate="3">In most of the world children born to foreign parents are not automatically granted citizenship.</span></p>
</a>



